\subtree{
\title{Quality Checklist}
\p{Before deploying any rule:}

\ul{
\li{[ ] Name follows \code{\startverb {CATEGORY}_{PLATFORM}_{FAMILY}_{VARIANT}_{DATE}\stopverb} format}
\li{[ ] Description starts with "Detects" and explains what/how}
\li{[ ] All required metadata present (author, reference, date)}
\li{[ ] Strings are unique (not API names, common paths, or format strings)}
\li{[ ] All strings have 4+ bytes with good atom potential}
\li{[ ] Base64 modifier only on strings with 3+ characters}
\li{\startverb [ ] Regex patterns have escaped `{` and valid escape sequences\stopverb}
\li{[ ] Condition starts with cheap checks (filesize, magic bytes)}
\li{[ ] Rule matches all target samples}
\li{[ ] Rule produces zero matches on goodware corpus}
\li{[ ] \code{\startverb yr check\stopverb} passes with no errors}
\li{[ ] \code{\startverb yr fmt --check\stopverb} passes (consistent formatting)}
\li{[ ] Linter passes with no errors}
\li{[ ] Peer review completed}
}
}

